</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8BA8F17CBA7EFA13D697CA3231D5A4E9" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" type="macn">
<paragraph id="4A171A151D4BE7BA45DD03807AA5B5DE" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">MACN.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="769C06EBE0899ED0007B131993F823C9" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">
A female syntype in the Berg collection with a green label with the inscription &quot;Buenos Aires.&quot; a red label with the inscription 
<normalizedToken id="63CDC56BAE8D10503E70DA8D9346F25A" originalValue="“TYPUS,”">&quot;TYPUS,&quot;</normalizedToken>
a white label with the inscription 
<normalizedToken id="543C41F3A0612A439AA477ECE8F2D5B2" originalValue="“Typus”">&quot;Typus&quot;</normalizedToken>
and a red label with the inscription &quot;Lectotype ♀ 
<taxonomicName id="0139F80558DF2057CBB23C63723F296A" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Halysidota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Halysidota sertata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sertata">Halysidota sertata</taxonomicName>
Berg designated by Beccacece, Vincent &amp; Navarro.&quot; We hereby designate it as lectotype. [MACN]. It is in very poor condition, with no antennae, both wings are damaged and the right wings are folded backwards (Fig. 12).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EDE9B6CDA982FB9969CC94F7BFFAAE8A" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="884BAC84609D68CF55840A5B837FBC92" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="240CB68837A8AAE96CA88C16F32B88B7" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">
Berg stated that the male specimen is preserved in the collection of M. Ruscheweyh. In 
<bibRefCitation id="FEFAD56ADCB8A55FBEE9170BFD07A0BB" author="Horn, W" journalOrPublisher="Akademie der Landwirtschaftswissenschaften der Deutschen Demokratischen Republik edition, Berlin" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" title="Collectiones entomologicae. Ein Kompendium ueber den Verbleib emtomologischer Sammlungen der Welt bis 1960" year="1990">Horn et al. (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, a part of this collection may be in ZMHB. After verification by the second author, no corresponding specimen was located in this institution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
